<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1911-08-13T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1911-08-13T00:00:00-05:00" n="355" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d355">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 838.00/647.</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the <gloss type="to">American Minister</gloss>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram—Paraphrase.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1911-08-13"><hi rend="italic">August 13,
                                1911</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>Referring to legation’s August 12, Mr. Knox informs Mr. Furniss that the
                            Department considers it most important to have the assurances referred
                            to made to him in writing.</p>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>